Woodstock Library invites pre-school and Grade R learners to its South African Library Week celebration­. This integrated programme will be held on Thursday 22 March at the library, on the corner of Aberdeen and Clyde streets from 10:00 to 12:00. The theme is “Libraries: Heart of the communities”. Children will enjoy various activities including storytelling and face painting. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  